Lenzing Owner B&C May Buy Stakes in Austrian Firms, Presse Says

-- B y   B o r i s   G r o e n d a h l
-- 
2011-02-24T06:13:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/lenzing-owner-b-c-may-buy-stakes-in-austrian-firms-presse-says.html
B&C Industrieholding, the owner of  Lenzing AG , may buy stakes in Austrian companies seeking new key
shareholders, B&C Chief Executive Officer Michael Junghans was
quoted as saying in Austrian daily newspaper Die Presse.  The group, which also owns stakes in Semperit AG and  Allgemeine Baugesellschaft Porr AG , has around 100 companies "on
its radar screen," including  Wienerberger AG  and  Zumtobel AG ,
Die Presse reported, citing an "unofficial list."  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Boris Groendahl at 
 bgroendahl@bloomberg.net  